                                                                                                                                   Six injured in grenade attack

     A STAFF REPORTER 
               
	Guwahati, Jan. 14: Six persons, including three CRPF personnel and a traffic constable, were injured when suspected Ulfa militants lobbed a grenade at a police patrol near the zilla parishad office in Morigaon town around 7.20pm today. 
    
	A group of CRPF personnel from 109 battalion were frisking vehicles when suspected rebels lobbed a grenade from a nearby bylane. 
    
	The injured were rushed to Morigaon civil hospital. The CRPF personnel and traffic constable were released after first aid. 
    
	Two civilians, Siraj Ali and Harakanta Deka, were admitted to the hospital with splinter injuries. While Ali is out of danger, Dekas condition is stated to be critical. 
    
	In an unrelated development, a former Bodo Liberation Tigers militant, Kabiranjan Basumatary, was shot at by an unidentified gunman at Bhatarmari under Kokrajhar police station at 6.30pm. Basumatary, who was on his motorcycle, escaped unhurt.
    
	Militant arrested
    
	Personnel of 2 Bihar Regiment last night apprehended a self-styled corporal of Ulfas 28th battalion , Bitupan Moran, from Rajgarh tea estate in Tinsukia district and seized a cache of ammunition and explosives from him. 
    
	 The army said it recovered 1kg explosives; six live rounds of AK 56 and 15 rounds of assorted ammunition. He is an explosives expert of Ulfa. 
    
	Another source said he was picked up by the soldiers three days back and handed over to police only today.
                                                                     
